Notts County have appointed Ricardo Moniz as their new manager just a week after the club announced that he was unable to commit to the role .
The former Tottenham and Hamburg coach pulled out of the running due to ` family reasons ' at the end of March but moved to Meadow Lane on a three-year deal .
The 50-year-old Dutchman has confirmed that Dave Kevan will be Moniz 's assistant .